The paper deals with the problem of scene text retrieval, which involves understanding textual information in images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed model uses a CNN architecture, which is a common tool in computer vision (cs.CV) and deep learning (cs.LG). The model also involves text representation and processing, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with image databases and processing speed, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
